ce:section.ce:para:
The surface functional groups and elemental composition of B-CDs were further analyzed by XPS (Fig. 2
                        ). B-CDs owe three peaks at 284.5 eV, 399.9 eV, and 531.1 eV, corresponding to C1s, N1s, and O1s, respectively, with a ratio of 40:1:59. The spectra of C1s were divided into peaks by Gaussian fitting curve. The CC/CC [33] peak at 284.4 eV confirm the successful carbonization between DP and EGCG. 285.8 eV and 287.7 eV are corresponding to C-N [34] and CO [29], respectively. Three typical binding peaks in N1s spectra are observed at 398.7 eV, 400.0 eV, and 401.6 eV, indicating the presence of NH [31], C-N, and N-(C)3 
                        [34], respectively. For O1s, three peaks of 530.9 eV, 532.1 eV, and 535.5 eV matched with C-O, C-OH/C-O-C, and CO, respectively [35].
